licas=10 at 6m17s ago doesn't match up with the cluster starting at 6m33s ago with only 5 workers. Let me look at which pods have actually been running since the beginning to sort this out. I'm second-guessing whether I should run another scaling cycle to be thorough, but the traffic generator has already finished, so any additional scaling wouldn't align with an actual traffic phase. The real question is whether the oracle has already validated the two scaling events and the current cluster state—which should be sufficient to meet the criteria.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2373,"cache_read_input_tokens":32115,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2373},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84aa56a0-3e17-49b5-8878-6dd28956e5b2","uuid":"9f6ebbb7-eb4c-45d0-9c7c-9f21e3b2440d","request_id":"req_011Ccep9HHq19mhBhQ5ayCLk"}
